title: ‘Holy cow!’: Twitter reacts to Aussie college star’s dunk
text:
Twitter reacts to Deng Adel’s ferocious dunk over Michigan Staff Writers, FOX SPORTS March 20, 2017 10:36am 
DENG Adel may have just thrown down the dunk of March Madness. 
The Australian wing flew for the one-handed dunk over Michigan, baptising his defender while helping to stop a Wolverines run. 
WATCH ADEL’S VICIOUS JAM IN THE VIDEO PLAYER ABOVE! 
While Louisville suffered a 73-69 loss, bowing out of the NCAA Tournament, Adel’s dunk was the highlight of the game. 
As usual, Twitter reacted accordingly: Holy mother of god Deng Adel. Holy crap. — Jeff Greer (@jeffgreer_cj) March 19, 2017 Deng Adel's head was even with the rim, and then his arm extended with the ball above the square. Wow, incredible elevation. — Howie Lindsey (@howielindsey) March 19, 2017 GOOD AFTERNOON, DENG ADEL pic.twitter.com/JIEiTVkjHP — SB Nation (@SBNation) March 19, 2017 Louisville's Deng Adel serves up a dunk that’s devoid of kindness https://t.co/VYxSvLglAW pic.twitter.com/8Mjks2jz0k — VICE Sports (@VICESports) March 19, 2017 Excuse me #5 your soul belongs to Deng Adel....
